{"word":"Ἴακχος","slug":"Ἴακχος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Ἴακχος</b></el> <el>(Ἴακχος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἰαχέω'><el>ἰαχέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>Iacchus</i>, mystic name of Bacchus, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a festal song</i> in his honour, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}